 In a media statement issued by the South African Police Service, it was made known that a 17-year-old girl was kidnapped on the 7th of October. The girl’s family reported her disappearance after she allegedly went to fetch her younger sister but failed to return to her home in Mhluzi. A missing person inquiry was opened followed by a thorough search which resulted in the girl’s discovery on the 9th of October. Also read: Increase in kidnapping and murder of children in Mpumalanga The girl was kidnapped by two suspects who held her captive for two days until her rescue.
She was found in Extention 8, Mhluzi. •Anyone with information that could lead to the arrest of the suspects may contact Detective Constable John Phoku on 072 216 7505 or call the SAPS Crime Stop number on 08600 10111.  R10 000 reward for information ‘We should kill him’ – Truck driver hears how hijackers argue about his fate #TrafficUpdate: Avoid N4 near Machadodorp VIDEO: Machadodorp two granted bail  • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za